description: The MARAUDER VISR is built around the concept of hot-loadable tactical software modules optimized for particular situations. Modules are selected either by the onboard battle management system or the user.

name: Mark IV GEN1
description: A battered Mark IV helmet once worn by the Master Chief is the last thing that SPARTAN-IV candidates see before beginning their grueling evaluation and preliminary augmentation cycle.

name: Mark IV GEN1 Arcadia
description: A battered Mark IV helmet once worn by the Master Chief is the last thing that SPARTAN-IV candidates see before beginning their grueling evaluation and preliminary augmentation cycle.

name: Mark V Alpha
description: It is unclear who requested an integration check for the Mark V helmet with the latest GEN2 architecture, but engineers at Materials Group have been surprised at the MARK V ALPHA's near-parity with contemporary designs.

name: Mark V Alpha Reflex
description: It is unclear who requested an integration check for the Mark V helmet with the latest GEN2 architecture, but engineers at Materials Group have been surprised at the MARK V ALPHA's near-parity with contemporary designs.

name: Mark VI GEN1
description: The distinctive silhouette of the MARK VI GEN1 helmet remains one the most powerful symbols of the Human-Covenant War.

name: Mark VI GEN1 Scarred
description: Constructed with the utmost care and multiply redundant subsystems, MARK VI helmets can remain functional even after horrendous damage.

name: Mark VI Primus
description: Key features of the iconic MARK VI helmet design have been retained in newer permutations.

name: Mark VI Regent
description: Key features of the iconic MARK VI helmet design have been retained in newer permutations.

name: Maverick Jester
description: The custom operating system for the MAVERICK is efficiently coded and highly mutable; few realize that it is an iteration of software that Chalybs developed for their Covenant War-era Mjolnir suits.

name: Nightfall
description: Lessons learned on far-flung hellscapes have shaped the NIGHTFALL helmet into the best multi-environment system available.

name: Noble Honor
description: A significant update of the MK.V/K design, NOBLE helmets feature hardened battlenet uplinks and Chalybs' latest kinetic mesh networking admin tools.

name: Orbital Equinox
description: The Buffalo A-29 comm suite in the ORBITAL helmet works flawlessly with the ad-hoc and anarchic telecommunication networks found in many colonies.

name: Raider
description: RAIDER helmets were crafted to be physically intimidating, though its effectiveness is disputed.

name: Reaper Mortician
description: The maximum potential of the REAPER will only be unlocked after substantial improvements are made to the base Mjolnir techsuit.

name: Scout Outrider
description: Materials Group tested various form factors of the SCOUT helmet before settling on a sleek shape reminiscent of the MARK VI GEN1 model.

name: Shinobi Heartless
description: The SHINOBI core systems remain cryptic "black boxes" to UNSC analysts, despite ONI's successes in integrating the SHINOBI helmet with standard GEN2 Mjolnir techsuits and Spartan neural interfaces.

name: Technician
description: Effectively a cutting-edge techscanner array packed into a compact package, the aptly-named TECHNICIAN helmet allows the wearer to function as a mobile diagnostic center.

name: Technician Override
description: Effectively a cutting-edge techscanner array packed into a compact package, the aptly-named TECHNICIAN helmet allows the wearer to function as a mobile diagnostic center.

name: Venator Cestus
description: The latest VENATOR firmware incorporates a generalization of predictive targeting algorithms originally created to assist new Spartans in close-quarters combat.

name: Venator Thraex
description: The latest VENATOR firmware incorporates a generalization of predictive targeting algorithms originally created to assist new Spartans in close-quarters combat.

name: Void Dancer
description: The VOID DANCER does not meet all Mjolnir standards, sacrificing compatibility so that Emerson Tactical Systems can integrate its own black-box components.

name: Void Dancer Comet
description: The VOID DANCER does not meet all Mjolnir standards, sacrificing compatibility so that Emerson Tactical Systems can integrate its own black-box components.

name: War Master Augustan
description: The WAR MASTER's neural interface was intentionally throttled after early testing showed inexperienced Spartans would dangerously overextend themselves in combat due to the euphoric side-effects.

name: War Master Scipio
description: The WAR MASTER's neural interface was intentionally throttled after early testing showed inexperienced Spartans would dangerously overextend themselves in combat due to the euphoric side-effects.
